	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hail Friends!<BR>
 I, among many others, watched with interest Mr. Banegrivm's prophecies, actions, guild actions, successes, and failures whilst he was on Druzzil Ro.<BR>
 From what I gathered, we on Druzzil were usually 3 weeks to the day behind 4 other servers in common GM events. As you can imagine, it wouldn't be too hard to figure out what would happen next.. if it had already happened on another server. Banegrivm simply watched the boards here and at other sites, and like anyone else could have figured, heralded that it would soon be happening on his &lt;our&gt; server. ( I always got a kick out of that!)<BR>
 As a role-player, Bane was pretty cool. He stuck to his role 100%, and enjoyed doing it. And for that, a big round of applause as well!<BR>
 Banes fault lies within the fact that he took all the common information available, looked for a link between them, and compiled his opinions on these links as fact, when as such it was indeed his own opinion. He convinced many people on Druzzil &lt;as he had previously done on Fenin&gt; that he was in contact with 'imaginary' NPC's/ GM controlled characters and they were feeding him info on events about to unfold. As we all know, EQ is in fact partial to NO singular player, and these meetings with NPC's never in fact actually occured.<BR>
 I digest. One did in fact actually occur because a buddy of mine created a character, and fed Bane a bunch of nonsense info to see what would happen. Mr Banegrivm shortly announced that he had been spoken to by the Gods &lt;grin&gt;. Ok, maybe that was a mean thing to do, but it was funny as hell to watch 1FOL go nuts with new info from my buddies lil joke.<BR>
 Basically, Banegrivm is an all around hardcore Roleplayer with aspirations to be part of Norrath's permanant history. I don't see anything wrong with this, other than the fact that he SHOULD clarify when he is stating an opinion, or actual Norrathian History. This would help those others of us that are compiling our own notes not to be misled when we don't recognize opinion. <BR>
 I took part in one mini-event with Bane when we were in our 40's. He and I were in GFaye and some GM type NPC's asked us to go whomp up on Castle Mistmoore. Banegrivm, a few of his 1FOL'ers, a buncha noobs, and myself &lt;not a 1FOL'er nor have ever been lol&gt; went in a WRECKED that joint! We all had a blast and I have to say Bane and his gaggle did a great job at roleplaying.<BR>
 Hey, go read his writ. It make for great enjoyment and is interestingly written. Just remember that he adds alot of his own theories and opinions to the many facts he supplies.<BR>
 Although I have to a point defended Banegrivm, I hope I have also shown that he does as well in fact manipulate his writings with his own opinions. But ya know what? I haven't seen any of these blatant flamers do as much research as he has.. and if they have, I'm apologize and congratulate them! Please post what you have found too!<BR>
<BR>
 Cinte Wayward,<BR>
 55 Outrider<BR>
 Druzzil Ro<BR>
  
